@jaye___718 today’s situation is different from WWII. Back then, aid was part of a united effort against an existential threat. Now, there are valid concerns about the long-term consequences of such aid and its impact on domestic priorities.

As for Albanians, many of us fled the brutal Communist regime, not right-wing persecution. Supporting secure immigration policies doesn’t equate to siding with fascists—it’s about balance and protecting national interests.

Finally, dismissing concerns as 'MAGA propaganda' doesn’t engage with the real issues. Many people questioning current policies are doing so out of genuine concern, not just repeating talking points.
